frameDefinitions: A Wearer removes an item of Clothing from a Body_location (the part of the body that the Clothing is prototypically worn on.)
A Social_event occurs at which Attendees are present to conduct a social function or joint activity.
This frame concerns people being in an altered mental state that is induced by an Intoxicant.
This frames describes a social event where there may or may not be a permanent or semi-permanent relationship between participants.
Words in this frame name the different parts of the calendric cycle, both man-made and natural.
The words in this frame have to do with people and the personal Relationships they are or can be a part of.
frameExamples: Walking on sand is better if you <t>take</t> <t>off</t> your shoes. INI
Sue threw a <t>party</t> for Bob's birthday.
Our <t>date</t> yesterday was interrupted by my ex-boyfriend!
Jo's mother will visit on this coming <t>Tuesday</t>.
And of course that drippy <t><fex name='Partner_1'>boyfriend</fex></t> of hers backed her up.
listRoleDefinitions: The individual who begins the action wearing the <fen>Clothing</fen> and ends the action without it.
The item that the <fen>Wearer</fen> is initially wearing but then removes.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which a <fen>Wearer</fen> undresses.
The location at which the <fen>Wearer</fen> undresses an item of <fen>Clothing</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Social_event</fen> itself.
<fen>Attendee</fen> is used for the people who come to the <fen>Social_event</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Social_event</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Social_event</fen> occurs.
The mental state of the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is changed by an <fen>Intoxicant</fen> .
The <fen>Intoxicant</fen> alters the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s mental experience.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> becomes intoxicated.
The <fen>Attendees</fen> are the collectively construed participants of the social event.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the social event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the social event occurs.
<fen>Relative_time</fen> is used for the word or words that locate the time with respect to an identifiable reference point.
<fen>Whole</fen> is used for the larger unit of which the target word names a part.
The calendric unit that is denoted. LUs in this frame all denote the <fen>Unit</fen>.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is realized as the subject of verbs in active form sentences, or of adjectives in predicative uses.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is not expressed as the external argument.
The joint construal of both <fen>Partners</fen> in the <fen>Relationship</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The suspects</fex> had to strip publically and endure several blasts from a firehose.
The department <fex><t>picnic</t></fex> was lots of fun.
Jo's mother will visit <fex> this coming</fex> Tuesday.
Jo fled in the early morning <fex>of  Sunday December 15</fex>.
